MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

What changed in docs/schema/06-modifiers.md:

- Every modifier entry now carries an explicit implementation status:
  ✅ implemented & used, 🟡 implemented/contract but unused, ⚠️ described
  but engine doesn't read it (debt), 🗑 legacy/forbidden in new data.

- Added 7 modifier fields that exist in data but were missing from the
  registry: 'armorConstraint', 'carryWeightFixed' (was implied via
  'carryWeightLimit'), 'ncrInfantryWeaponIds' (tagged legacy → migrates
  to 'weaponDamageBonus'), 'robotBodyPlan', 'robotRules', 'robotType',
  'attributes' (legacy form). Each placed in the right section (new
  § 1.9 for robot-specific, new § 1.10 for legacy).

- Marked 'skillModifiers' as ⚠️: engine does not read it yet. Removed
  the 'TODO: T-3 → canonical' notes that were stale (canonical is done).
  Added explicit contract: this is THE field for 'perk gives +N to a
  skill' / 'chem gives +N to a skill'.

- Added new contract entries that don't exist in data yet but fix the
  open design questions the owner asked:
    * 'skillBonusChoice' 🟡 — 'perk gives +N to a skill of the player's
      choice' (resolves to skillModifiers on the active perk instance).
    * 'attributePointsBonus' ⚠️ — clearly noted that the perk
      'Intense Training' currently works through a hardcoded check on
      the Russian name in PerksAndTraitsScreen.js (and even reads a
      non-existent perk.modifiers.attributeBonus). This is the debt to
      retire when the aggregator lands.

- Clarified that the 'weaponDamageBonus' contract is asserted by the
  existing test suite (domain/weaponDamageBonus.test.js) but the
  matching readers in domain/traits.js are not yet implemented — the
  tests are red until that lands.

- Removed stale '(TODO T-3 → canonical)' notes on forcedSkills and
  skillModifiers — canonical UPPER_SNAKE_CASE is now enforced by
  domain/contract.skills.test.js.

- New § 3.2 introduces the contract for a single aggregator function:
  domain/modifiers.js#aggregateModifiers(sources) — the only place that
  walks origin / trait / active perks / active chem effects and produces
  a merged map. No consumer code is allowed to read trait.modifiers.X
  or perk.modifiers.X directly outside this module. Today's fragmented
  readers (getTraitAttributeBonus, getRemainingAttributePoints, …) are
  documented as transitional.

- New § 3.3 gives ready-to-use recipes for the owner's two concrete
  questions: 'how to write a perk that gives +N to a skill' and 'will
  Intense Training work with the new format' — both reduce to
  modifiers: { skillModifiers: {...} } / { attributePointsBonus: N }
  once the aggregator lands.

No code changes. This is the contract that the upcoming
domain/modifiers.js refactor will implement against.
